A taxi operator sterilises his taxi to curb the spread of infection. A taxi operator wears a mask and gloves while transporting passengers in an attempt to curb the spread of COVID-19, People queue in Cape Town to get their final shopping in before the 21-day lockdown. People queue in Mitchells Plain to buy liquor before the 21-day lockdown. A Cape Town school is making sure its pupils will have food over the 21-day period. President Cyril Ramaphosa has been attending a virtual G20 emergency meeting on a global response to the coronavirus pandemic. President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses SAPS members ahead of the national lockdown starting at midnight. President Cyril Ramaphosa addressed the SAPS before their deployment.